All Classes and Interfaces

Class
Description
Card
Represents a card in the game.
ComputerPlayer
ComputerPlayer represents an AI Player in Parade.
Deck
Represents a standard deck of cards used in the game.
Difficulty
The difficulty level of AI Players.
Game
Represents the main controller for the game logic and flow.
GameClient
The GameClient class is responsible for managing the client-side logic of the online game.
GameLogic
Handles the core gameplay mechanics and turn-based logic for the Parade card game.
GameServer
The GameServer class is responsible for managing the server-side logic of the online game.
HighScore
A simple tracker for player high scores.
HighScoreDatabase
Manages the high score data for the game.
OnlineGameLogic
The OnlineGameLogic class manages the core game logic for an online multiplayer game.
Parade
Handles everything going on in the Parade row during the game.
Player
Represents each player in the game.
Scoring
Handles the end-of-game scoring logic for both local and online games.
SocketPacket
Constructs a new SocketPacket object for communication between the server and clients.
SoundPlayer
Manages audio playback and volume control for the game.
TurnManager
Helper class to keep track of whose turn it is during the game.
